    "intro": "Interpretation asks what Exodus 17 means — what the author intends in his historical context, how the two episodes function as a unified theological argument, and how the New Testament and canonical tradition receive these events. The movements below trace the chapter's argument from Israel's quarrel at Massah to the altar of Yahweh-Nissi, attending to the chapter's place in the larger Exodus narrative and its forward reach into apostolic interpretation.",
